<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
The report of this species is a new distribution record to Wuyi Mountains and had been well described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I." journalOrPublisher="Scopolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" pagination="1 - 122" refId="B7867379" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P., Shimizu, T., 2008. Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia 64: 1 - 122" title="Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae)" volume="64" year="2008">Sivec et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
and we defined our specimens as 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. yangdingi" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="yangdingi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. yangdingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after we checked the holotype of this species. Head pale brown, slightly wider than pronotum; compound eyes dark; antennae and mouth-parts pale brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8002492" captionText="Figure 8. Rhopalopsole yangdingi Sivec &amp; Harper, 2008. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711852" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">8</figureCitation>
A). Tergum 10 bearing a large central plate and the hind margin strongly sclerotized. Epiproct stocky, terminating in a trilobed tip, the middle is round, two other lobes are corners of epiproct (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8002492" captionText="Figure 8. Rhopalopsole yangdingi Sivec &amp; Harper, 2008. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711852" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
